WEBVTT

00:36.436 --> 00:40.473
[birds squawking]

00:58.625 --> 01:00.527
BOY: Come on, Javi,
we're gonna be late.

01:00.593 --> 01:03.029
- Come on, let's go.
- BOY 2: Hurry, Javi.

01:03.129 --> 01:03.430
Come on.

01:03.530 --> 01:05.598
Here.

01:12.806 --> 01:18.745
♪♪♪

01:27.921 --> 01:29.489
Morning, guys.

02:01.187 --> 02:02.522
POLICEMAN: We're doing
everything in our power.

02:02.589 --> 02:06.726
Hey, Costa, why are you here?
Did you miss me or what?

02:06.793 --> 02:07.627
Nine kids have
disappeared from this area

02:07.727 --> 02:10.096
in the past ten years.

02:10.163 --> 02:11.464
Ontinyent,
Alcoi, Macastre.

02:11.564 --> 02:12.966
Fourteen and 15 years old!

02:13.032 --> 02:14.234
I'm sure they're related
to my daughter's case.

02:14.334 --> 02:16.569
We don't know, that, Mario.
We don't know.

02:16.636 --> 02:18.371
But we're taking
the logical steps, here.

02:18.438 --> 02:20.240
Do you know how many cases
we get at the end of the summer

02:20.306 --> 02:22.008
- of couples eloping?
- My daughter didn't elope.

02:22.075 --> 02:24.911
- Oh.
- And neither have her friends.

02:25.011 --> 02:26.112
Really, Ramon?
You know her very well.

02:26.212 --> 02:28.648
You know she would never
do such a thing--

02:28.715 --> 02:30.683
I do, but I also know
how to do my job, Mario.

02:30.750 --> 02:32.118
Look, it's not
that easy to kidnap

02:32.185 --> 02:34.888
three girls in a nightclub
that was overflowing, okay?

02:34.954 --> 02:38.158
- No one saw anything.
- Right.

02:38.224 --> 02:40.793
- But...
- Mario.

02:40.894 --> 02:41.928
Mario. Please.

02:44.397 --> 02:45.665
I would be just as upset
if one of my kids went missing.

02:45.765 --> 02:48.134
You have to understand him.
It's natural for him--

02:48.201 --> 02:51.171
Today's my day off. You want
to go fishing or anything?

02:51.237 --> 02:52.605
We're not 15, Costa.

02:52.672 --> 02:53.573
...this situation
must be killing him.

02:53.640 --> 02:56.576
I'm sorry...

02:56.643 --> 02:58.478
we can plan
for something next week.

02:58.545 --> 03:01.447
I know you're leaving... okay?

03:01.514 --> 03:03.082
We should go through
the file again, Mario.

03:03.149 --> 03:04.784
Sure.

03:07.554 --> 03:08.955
Sweetie, what are you
doing here?

03:09.055 --> 03:11.124
I saw unmoored boats
at the docks,

03:11.191 --> 03:13.726
and there's a north wind coming.
You should send someone.

03:13.793 --> 03:15.728
You don't stop, do you?
Get some rest, honey.

03:15.795 --> 03:18.565
Yes, Dad, I'll do that.

03:27.440 --> 03:30.276
Ah...ah, sir.
Can I help you?

03:31.477 --> 03:33.146
Hey, did you hear me?

03:33.246 --> 03:34.814
Tell me who you're looking for.

03:37.517 --> 03:40.987
Uh...hey...

03:41.087 --> 03:42.455
Where are you going?

03:42.522 --> 03:44.824
- Did anybody order food?
- [chuckles]

03:46.226 --> 03:47.827
Hey, you, get the hell
out of this office. Come on.

03:47.927 --> 03:50.163
Lieutenant Zhou,
Central Unit.

03:51.397 --> 03:53.967
You should have been notified
we were coming.

03:54.033 --> 03:56.236
Sorry, no one informed us
it'd be today.

03:56.302 --> 03:58.204
Now you're informed.

03:58.271 --> 03:59.872
Sergeant Ramon Costas.

03:59.973 --> 04:02.709
"Yellow Fellow" or "Miyagi"
or even "Spring Roll."

04:02.809 --> 04:03.843
The sooner you get the jokes
out of the way,

04:03.910 --> 04:06.713
the sooner
we can start, hmm?

04:06.813 --> 04:08.748
There are three girls missing.

04:10.149 --> 04:11.985
Are there any questions?

04:12.085 --> 04:13.486
No.

04:13.553 --> 04:16.289
Good.
Very, very good.

04:19.993 --> 04:23.196
Now you keep quiet,
all right?

04:29.569 --> 04:32.772
[school bell rings]

05:12.545 --> 05:14.714
Who did this?

05:19.952 --> 05:22.121
Who did it?

05:22.188 --> 05:24.791
Who did this?!

05:29.796 --> 05:30.830
JAVI:
She's not dead.

05:30.930 --> 05:34.534
[sobbing]
She's not dead!

05:34.600 --> 05:36.302
Why aren't you in class?

05:36.402 --> 05:38.871
[Javi crying]

05:40.640 --> 05:43.109
Who wrote it?

05:43.209 --> 05:45.945
- I want to know who did it!
- He did.

05:49.215 --> 05:50.650
[cries out]

05:50.717 --> 05:52.685
- [grunting]
- Enough.

05:52.752 --> 05:54.454
- [grunting continues]
- Enough!

05:54.520 --> 05:56.189
I said, that's enough!

05:56.289 --> 05:58.424
No, hey!
Stop it right now.

05:58.524 --> 05:59.926
Get up, punk!

06:05.998 --> 06:06.966
Go to my office!

06:19.078 --> 06:21.614
Hello. Does anybody copy?
Over.

06:25.918 --> 06:27.954
Hello.
Does anybody copy? Over.

06:32.125 --> 06:34.394
My daughter disappeared
three months ago

06:34.494 --> 06:35.695
from Almanzora.

06:35.762 --> 06:37.196
Brunette with long hair.

06:37.263 --> 06:38.631
She was wearing a black skirt
and a red top.

06:38.731 --> 06:41.667
Is anyone there? Over.

06:46.372 --> 06:47.840
She was with two friends.

06:47.907 --> 06:50.009
They were last seen
in the night club Paraíso.

06:50.076 --> 06:51.110
If anyone knows anything,

06:51.210 --> 06:53.713
please contact
the police station.

06:53.813 --> 06:54.080
Over.

07:00.920 --> 07:04.157
Now we place the copper wire
with the magnet

07:04.223 --> 07:06.692
on one of the ends
of the potato,

07:06.759 --> 07:08.027
and the other
on the other end.

07:08.127 --> 07:10.630
So why, do you think,
the potato...

07:10.730 --> 07:11.931
WOMAN: I am horrified.

07:11.998 --> 07:15.034
I just can't believe it,
honestly.

07:15.134 --> 07:17.270
- Who wants to tell me?
- [sighs]

07:17.370 --> 07:19.105
Anyone?

07:19.205 --> 07:21.073
What is wrong with you?
Have you lost your mind?

07:21.174 --> 07:24.277
That family has always
been so good to us.

07:24.343 --> 07:27.680
How could you even think of
such a horrible prank?

07:29.749 --> 07:31.517
You've got nothing to say?

07:31.584 --> 07:33.252
Go get in the car, please.

07:33.319 --> 07:33.986
I'm gonna talk to him.

07:46.566 --> 07:48.601
To be honest,

07:48.668 --> 07:52.004
it was very funny.

07:52.071 --> 07:54.073
Hmm?

07:54.173 --> 07:55.875
Absolutely side-splitting.

07:57.210 --> 07:58.511
[chuckles]

07:59.445 --> 08:00.947
[grunts]

08:01.047 --> 08:03.282
I don't give two shits
about your life.

08:03.349 --> 08:04.917
I'm not your father,
but don't you ever

08:04.984 --> 08:06.719
upset your mother
again, okay?

08:07.954 --> 08:09.388
Get up, asshole.

08:10.523 --> 08:11.924
Come on.

08:16.629 --> 08:18.064
Hello, does anyone copy?

08:18.164 --> 08:20.733
My daughter disappeared
three months ago

08:20.800 --> 08:22.435
from Almanzora.

08:22.535 --> 08:23.803
Over.

08:25.505 --> 08:30.042
[radio static]

08:30.109 --> 08:31.444
[sighs]

08:33.713 --> 08:36.115
Her name is Sandra.

08:36.215 --> 08:39.352
For her, enclosed spaces
are excruciating.

08:42.455 --> 08:43.022
Humid places, too.

08:45.558 --> 08:46.792
She doesn't like the dark.

08:48.127 --> 08:50.263
<i>MAN: This is Charlie,
Macastre Station.</i>

08:50.363 --> 08:52.665
<i>Connor, you copy? Over.</i>

08:52.765 --> 08:53.933
This is Connor, I copy. Over.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.736
<i>I heard your call a week ago.</i>

08:56.802 --> 08:58.170
<i>I've been waiting
for you to call again.</i>

08:58.237 --> 09:01.774
<i>My son also disappeared
from Macastre,</i>

09:01.841 --> 09:03.843
<i>two hours away
from your station.</i>

09:03.910 --> 09:05.811
<i>He was with his girlfriend
and a friend,</i>

09:05.878 --> 09:08.481
<i>but... [sighs] ...it'd be
better to speak face to face.</i>

09:08.548 --> 09:10.216
Charlie, I copy. Over.

09:10.283 --> 09:13.052
♪♪♪

09:16.989 --> 09:19.525
CONNOR: I'm a sailor.
That's why I have a radio.

09:19.592 --> 09:22.161
I like watching over my kids
when I'm out there fishing.

09:22.228 --> 09:23.563
CHARLIE: Of course.

09:23.629 --> 09:25.798
I bought mine
when my son disappeared.

09:25.865 --> 09:29.001
How long has he been missing?

09:29.068 --> 09:31.237
Three years now.

09:31.304 --> 09:33.072
In October.

09:33.172 --> 09:35.408
They went to town
to the carnival rides

09:35.474 --> 09:37.076
and we never saw him again.

09:41.814 --> 09:44.483
So, you haven't heard
from them or...

09:47.119 --> 09:47.954
That's the worst part.

09:48.054 --> 09:50.089
There's--there's
nowhere I can go

09:50.156 --> 09:54.627
to put a couple of flowers
or say a prayer.

09:55.795 --> 09:58.130
But I don't care about that.

09:58.197 --> 09:59.765
But his mother...

10:01.867 --> 10:02.969
his mother would have loved
to do so.

10:06.806 --> 10:09.475
Well, doesn't matter now.

10:09.575 --> 10:11.010
She also left me
some time ago, so...

10:13.212 --> 10:15.114
Cancer.

10:15.214 --> 10:16.148
It is what it is.

10:16.248 --> 10:19.385
Yeah.
But what did the police say?

10:19.485 --> 10:21.087
I mean, they must have
a theory, right?

10:21.153 --> 10:22.655
They'll be shitting
their slacks

10:22.722 --> 10:24.290
when I disclose
the truth, you know?

10:25.691 --> 10:27.293
You didn't happen to tell them
you were coming, right?

10:27.360 --> 10:31.664
They're all up to their necks,
those motherfuckers.

10:31.764 --> 10:33.566
I mean,
them and everyone else.

10:33.633 --> 10:35.134
What do you mean, everyone?

10:35.201 --> 10:36.802
Those in power.

10:36.869 --> 10:37.670
The military,
the intelligence agency.

10:37.770 --> 10:39.972
They're all bastards!

10:40.039 --> 10:42.174
The government bugged
my entire house.

10:42.241 --> 10:45.011
But they can't fool me.
They can't fool me, no.

10:45.077 --> 10:46.479
[breathing heavily]

10:46.545 --> 10:48.648
[stammers]
Let me show you a secret.

10:48.714 --> 10:50.449
But stay here--don't move.

10:51.550 --> 10:52.918
It's like a jigsaw.
Is it here?

10:52.985 --> 10:55.388
I know it has to be here
somewhere.

10:55.488 --> 10:57.590
God damn it!

10:58.424 --> 11:00.626
It should be here. Agh.

11:00.726 --> 11:02.828
I know I left it somewhere.

11:06.532 --> 11:09.669
♪♪♪

11:34.126 --> 11:36.762
- Happy birthday.
- What is it?

11:36.829 --> 11:38.464
Open it.

11:42.435 --> 11:44.003
It's your favorite movie,
right?

11:45.204 --> 11:46.906
In two months, they'll be
releasing the sequel.

11:47.573 --> 11:50.443
In Valencia.

11:50.509 --> 11:51.944
Not yet in this town.

11:53.279 --> 11:54.613
Well, you can come visit me.

11:54.680 --> 11:56.782
I'll get us tickets.

11:57.850 --> 11:59.719
When are you leaving?

11:59.785 --> 12:02.722
Maybe Monday or Tuesday.
I need to plan it.

12:04.724 --> 12:05.691
Forget about it for now, Javi.

12:05.758 --> 12:07.927
I thought you liked
your job here.

12:07.993 --> 12:09.762
And I do.

12:09.829 --> 12:12.531
But I believe this new job

12:12.598 --> 12:13.632
will be even better.

12:13.733 --> 12:16.869
Do you understand it?

12:16.969 --> 12:18.471
Thank you.

12:18.571 --> 12:19.972
Javi, please wait.

12:20.039 --> 12:21.307
Javi! Javi.

12:21.407 --> 12:22.608
What do you want me to say now?

12:23.442 --> 12:25.144
Get the hell out of here.

12:25.244 --> 12:26.679
Whatever!

12:28.547 --> 12:30.216
Javi, please.

12:30.282 --> 12:32.952
- [sniffling]
- Come here. There.

12:39.024 --> 12:40.426
Look at me.

12:41.594 --> 12:43.863
She'll be okay.

12:43.963 --> 12:45.765
That's a promise, all right?
Be strong.

12:47.600 --> 12:49.068
Gil Pérez?

13:53.265 --> 13:55.267
BEA: I'm going
to the police station!

13:55.367 --> 13:57.570
ROCA: You're going to your room,
just as I said 30 minutes ago!

13:57.636 --> 13:59.238
BEA:
No, I'm not going to my room!

13:59.305 --> 14:00.172
ROCA: If you put one foot
outside this house,

14:00.239 --> 14:02.041
you'll be grounded for a month!

14:02.107 --> 14:03.375
BEA: Oh, my God,
what are you saying?

14:03.442 --> 14:04.810
ROCA: Go to your room!

14:04.877 --> 14:06.145
Where do you think
you're going?

14:06.245 --> 14:08.681
I'm going sailing or are you
forbidding me that, too?

14:28.634 --> 14:29.969
[thuds, clatter]

14:38.744 --> 14:41.447
Hey, do you need help?

14:41.513 --> 14:44.283
[heavy breathing]

14:44.350 --> 14:45.784
Hello?

14:45.885 --> 14:49.855
[heavy breathing continues]

14:53.592 --> 14:55.227
Hey, hey, what's wrong?

14:55.327 --> 14:57.363
- Hey, what happened?
- [whispers] Sugar.

14:57.429 --> 14:59.832
- What?
- I need sugar.

14:59.932 --> 15:02.868
[panting]

15:37.002 --> 15:40.372
Um, here.
I found a clean towel for you.

15:43.309 --> 15:44.677
Thank you.

15:47.046 --> 15:48.113
[chuckles]

15:54.720 --> 15:57.556
[fly buzzing]

16:04.663 --> 16:06.932
[clatter]

16:10.636 --> 16:13.105
[rats chittering]

16:17.076 --> 16:19.478
What the hell are you
doing here?

16:21.146 --> 16:22.881
I'm so--I'm so sorry.
I didn't mean to upset you.

16:22.948 --> 16:23.949
You're in it too, aren't you?

16:24.049 --> 16:25.551
Where's my son?
Tell me!

16:25.651 --> 16:26.986
No, I'm just a father,

16:27.086 --> 16:28.687
and everything
I told you is true.

16:28.754 --> 16:30.122
Tell me where my son is,
or I'll shoot you!

16:30.189 --> 16:32.391
I swear to God
I'm gonna shoot you now!

16:32.491 --> 16:32.992
I'll shoot your brains out!

16:33.092 --> 16:35.127
I don't think so.

16:36.095 --> 16:39.798
[distant church bell ringing]

16:48.807 --> 16:51.143
I didn't know
you were diabetic.

16:51.243 --> 16:52.745
I've only told Olivia.

16:52.845 --> 16:54.713
And obviously my dad, too.

16:55.814 --> 16:57.883
But why would you hide it?

16:57.950 --> 16:59.952
I don't think
it's a bad thing.

17:00.052 --> 17:02.888
It makes people think
I'm weak,

17:02.955 --> 17:05.624
- and that's not true.
- Yeah, I know.

17:05.724 --> 17:05.991
I saw that from a mile away.

17:09.294 --> 17:12.064
If it were up to my dad,
I would stay locked up

17:12.164 --> 17:13.866
in a cage till I was
an old woman.

17:13.966 --> 17:15.934
Is that why you were arguing?

17:17.202 --> 17:18.971
We were arguing
because of you, Javi.

17:24.810 --> 17:26.311
I saw something
in the backside of Paraíso

17:26.412 --> 17:29.214
- the day of the party.
- Really? Something like what?

17:29.281 --> 17:31.150
I don't know,
like a glimmer, I guess.

17:31.250 --> 17:33.719
It was something
like a lit cigarette.

17:33.786 --> 17:35.120
Someone was smoking
on the cliff?

17:35.187 --> 17:36.688
No, I don't know. It could've
been the eyes of a cat

17:36.755 --> 17:39.091
or another animal.

17:44.596 --> 17:47.032
My father won't let me
tell this to the police.

17:47.132 --> 17:49.234
He says that person could've
also spotted me.

17:49.334 --> 17:51.603
Hmm. I think
he's right, though.

17:52.771 --> 17:54.073
You shouldn't get involved.

17:54.173 --> 17:55.074
Javi,
we're missing three girls.

17:59.511 --> 18:02.881
♪♪♪

18:13.358 --> 18:16.095
Four-stroke,
with self-propulsion,

18:16.161 --> 18:18.597
and sports suspension.
Oh, my.

18:18.664 --> 18:20.065
It reaches
12 miles per hour, easy.

18:20.165 --> 18:21.800
Yeah, right, that's rad,
but are you in or not?

18:21.867 --> 18:23.669
Quino, are you having dinner?

18:23.769 --> 18:25.204
Of course!

18:25.270 --> 18:27.906
Dude, we can't go to Paraíso.
We won't get in!

18:28.006 --> 18:28.607
- Have you lost your mind?
- Who said anything

18:28.674 --> 18:31.276
about getting in?

18:31.343 --> 18:33.812
- [sighs]
- Do you have a thick rope?

18:33.879 --> 18:35.347
Stop, stop,
don't do that to yourself.

18:35.447 --> 18:36.882
Didn't you hear your mother?
Leave her alone, you bully.

18:36.949 --> 18:39.318
- And that goes for you too.
- Javi, sweetie, are you staying

18:39.384 --> 18:41.286
- for dinner?
- I can't, I'm sorry.

18:41.353 --> 18:43.088
- My dad is waiting for me.
- Today's his birthday, Mom.

18:43.155 --> 18:45.524
Oh, then you can't leave
without a piece of cake.

18:45.591 --> 18:47.960
[overlapping chatter]

18:51.530 --> 18:52.798
So, dude, can I count on you?

18:52.865 --> 18:54.800
- Have I ever let you down?
- Don't be such a bully!

18:54.867 --> 18:57.436
- Here, handsome.
- Thanks.

18:57.503 --> 18:59.371
- Want some?
- And hey, congratulations, son.

18:59.438 --> 19:01.406
- Thank you.
- ...happy birthday, dear.

19:01.473 --> 19:03.208
- Have a good evening.
- See you tomorrow.

19:03.275 --> 19:04.743
- Happy birthday, Javi!
- See you later!

19:04.843 --> 19:07.513
Here-- there, thank you.

19:07.613 --> 19:10.682
All my tables are always loaded
with your weird doodles.

19:10.749 --> 19:12.151
There you go.

19:12.251 --> 19:13.986
Are you kidding me?
This is art, Dad,

19:14.086 --> 19:15.754
and for that,
when I win an Oscar,

19:15.854 --> 19:17.256
I'm not dedicating it to you.

19:45.450 --> 19:47.753
Dad?

19:51.390 --> 19:52.824
Hello?

19:54.726 --> 19:56.495
Sandra?

19:56.562 --> 19:58.197
Surprise!
Javi's back!

19:59.765 --> 20:02.834
Why are you here? Mario!

20:02.935 --> 20:03.936
- Okay.
- What?

20:04.002 --> 20:04.870
Happy birthday! Surprise!

20:04.970 --> 20:08.574
- Congratulations!
- [laughter]

20:08.640 --> 20:10.475
- Who's got the present?
- Me!

20:10.542 --> 20:12.010
Here. Enjoy it, dear.

20:16.748 --> 20:18.584
Do you like it?

20:18.684 --> 20:20.953
We--we can totally return it
if you've already read it.

20:21.053 --> 20:23.055
- No, it's great.
- Don't worry.

20:23.121 --> 20:24.489
- Tada!
- A Game Boy!

20:24.556 --> 20:27.025
Oh, my God!

20:28.427 --> 20:29.795
It must've cost you a fortune.

20:30.996 --> 20:33.198
Come on, Javi, your candles.

20:33.265 --> 20:34.967
[laughs]
Before Dad starts crying.

20:41.206 --> 20:42.641
Now make a wish.

20:43.508 --> 20:48.480
♪♪♪

21:19.478 --> 21:20.912
[sighs]

21:31.423 --> 21:33.325
[distant dog barking]

21:33.392 --> 21:35.927
[blows]

21:46.171 --> 21:48.106
He said he had evidence
against--against the police,

21:48.206 --> 21:50.509
the intelligence agency,
and honestly,

21:50.609 --> 21:52.477
at first I thought
it was related to my daughter,

21:52.544 --> 21:54.846
but poor man has lost his mind.

21:57.049 --> 21:58.283
We'll talk to them again
when he calms down.

21:58.350 --> 22:00.952
Chances are he can lead us
to a logical clue.

22:03.455 --> 22:05.390
Is there anyone
who would like to hurt you?

22:05.490 --> 22:07.959
Hurt me? No.

22:08.794 --> 22:11.229
How about Commander Roca?

22:12.764 --> 22:15.067
[chuckles]
Who told you that?

22:15.167 --> 22:17.002
I mean, Roca's a difficult guy,
that's all.

22:18.170 --> 22:20.072
The man has a daughter almost
the same age as mine.

22:20.172 --> 22:22.474
One time I captured a man
with 13 babies

22:22.574 --> 22:23.909
buried in his garden.

22:25.010 --> 22:26.745
As we were digging up
the bodies,

22:26.845 --> 22:28.880
the judge let slip out,

22:28.947 --> 22:30.582
"This guy's a demon."

22:30.682 --> 22:32.484
[chuckles]

22:32.551 --> 22:35.487
The man heard, and you know
what he told us?

22:35.554 --> 22:37.089
- No.
- "As any man,

22:37.155 --> 22:40.726
I'm a carrier
and a bearer of all demons."

22:47.432 --> 22:49.000
Do you want a ride home?

22:49.067 --> 22:50.802
No. No.

22:52.003 --> 22:53.605
Thank you for earlier.

23:15.193 --> 23:17.496
It must be, like,
150 feet to the bottom.

23:17.562 --> 23:19.197
Hey! What's up?

23:19.264 --> 23:20.031
Tell me something!

23:20.132 --> 23:22.134
That fall is gruesome, dude.

23:22.200 --> 23:23.869
- Hey!
- He says he's terrified.

23:23.969 --> 23:26.304
No, man, I'm not saying that.

23:26.405 --> 23:28.573
But honestly, not just anyone
would go down there.

23:28.640 --> 23:30.909
[girl screams]

23:31.009 --> 23:33.211
What the hell?
Are you kidding me, girl?

23:33.278 --> 23:34.646
You're so heavy!

23:36.515 --> 23:38.884
Come help me, God damn it!

23:40.285 --> 23:43.054
♪♪♪

23:45.957 --> 23:49.127
- What happened?
- Hurry up!

23:49.194 --> 23:50.829
Bea!

23:53.165 --> 23:53.765
[screams]

23:53.832 --> 23:56.568
[grunts of exertion]

23:58.437 --> 24:00.238
What happened, guys?

24:00.305 --> 24:01.039
[grunts continue]

24:13.452 --> 24:15.654
Grab her already!
This is exhausting.

24:15.720 --> 24:17.322
Are you crazy?

24:17.389 --> 24:19.758
[all panting]

24:21.760 --> 24:23.795
Whose is this?

24:24.930 --> 24:26.731
- It's my sister's.
- QUINO: Hey!

24:26.798 --> 24:29.434
Are you sure of that, Javi?

24:29.534 --> 24:29.968
It was lying in the rocks.

24:35.640 --> 24:36.908
[overlapping chatter]

24:37.008 --> 24:39.244
- Calm down, boys, please.
- Please, listen to me.

24:39.311 --> 24:42.614
- [overlapping talk continues]
- What are you--calm down!

24:42.681 --> 24:43.849
Slow down! I can't
understand you, all right?

24:43.915 --> 24:46.284
- Javi.
- We found this

24:46.351 --> 24:48.086
lying on the cliffs
of Paraíso.

24:48.153 --> 24:49.654
It's my sister's.

24:49.721 --> 24:51.790
RAMON:
Good morning, Lieutenant.

24:53.925 --> 24:55.160
Did you go down there?

24:55.227 --> 24:57.729
- Are you crazy or what?
- [phone ringing]

25:00.432 --> 25:02.133
- [phone continues ringing]
- Local police station.

25:02.200 --> 25:03.168
Go ahead.

25:03.602 --> 25:05.437
No.

25:05.504 --> 25:07.239
No, no,
we have no information.

25:08.773 --> 25:10.542
Of course.

25:12.310 --> 25:13.945
Sure, sure.

25:14.045 --> 25:16.348
- [gasps]
- RAMON: No.

25:16.448 --> 25:18.083
Have you lost this?

25:21.853 --> 25:23.688
RAMON: Good,
we'll let you know.

25:23.755 --> 25:25.156
There's no need.
Thank you.

25:26.224 --> 25:27.692
Whew!
I almost shit my pants.

25:27.759 --> 25:29.027
I thought
he was gonna hit me.

25:29.127 --> 25:30.161
You know how many of these
badges exist out there?

25:30.228 --> 25:31.830
It's my sister's.
I'm telling you, please.

25:31.930 --> 25:34.833
I also want to find her, Javi.

25:34.933 --> 25:37.736
But that is why you shouldn't
waste our time anymore, please.

25:38.803 --> 25:40.906
You need to stop
playing detective.

26:00.959 --> 26:01.993
PAULA: Do you think
they got disoriented?

26:02.093 --> 26:05.664
That many?
There were 100, 200!

26:05.764 --> 26:09.034
Flying in all directions.

26:09.134 --> 26:11.002
I've never seen something
like this in my life.

26:12.504 --> 26:16.041
When a creature like that gets
close to the coast...

26:16.107 --> 26:18.677
the seagulls get distressed.

26:18.743 --> 26:21.913
Th-th-th-they lose all control.

26:22.013 --> 26:24.449
You speak about a creature.

26:24.516 --> 26:27.285
You mean a tuna,
something like that?

26:28.720 --> 26:32.424
Sharks, killer whales,

26:32.524 --> 26:34.292
apex predators.

26:36.494 --> 26:37.996
[bird cries]

26:50.609 --> 26:52.944
[cries continue]

26:55.614 --> 26:59.918
♪♪♪

27:02.721 --> 27:04.456
What are we looking for,
exactly?

27:04.522 --> 27:07.325
JAVI: Any book about this town,
about the time it was built.

27:07.392 --> 27:09.160
I want to know
what's beneath Paraíso.

27:09.227 --> 27:10.228
Ssh!

27:11.663 --> 27:13.331
QUINO: In what year
did the construction start?

27:13.398 --> 27:15.400
ALVARO: I think
the lighthouse was in 1800.

27:15.467 --> 27:16.568
About then or earlier.

27:16.635 --> 27:18.103
Look for something
about the pirate era.

27:18.203 --> 27:21.306
This coast has lots
of smuggler's caves.

27:21.406 --> 27:22.974
My grandpa told me that
when I was a little boy.

27:23.041 --> 27:24.676
Oh, your grandpa told you?
Great.

27:24.743 --> 27:27.212
He had Alzheimer's.

27:38.590 --> 27:39.958
Found something.

27:43.895 --> 27:45.030
What is it?

27:53.438 --> 27:56.041
It says that the town hall
used to be a hospital.

27:58.043 --> 28:00.211
And the House of Culture
was a military base.

28:03.014 --> 28:05.116
BEA: And that spa
on the outskirts

28:05.183 --> 28:06.785
used to be a lepers' hospital.

28:06.885 --> 28:08.153
ALVARO:
That place is totally rad.

28:08.253 --> 28:10.155
My parents took me
birdwatching by that place.

28:12.524 --> 28:13.992
- [chuckles]
- Here, that's Paraíso.

28:14.092 --> 28:16.294
It says that
in the 19th century,

28:16.361 --> 28:19.130
it was owned
by a textile tycoon.

28:19.197 --> 28:21.132
But does it say
anything else besides that?

28:22.467 --> 28:23.635
No.

28:23.735 --> 28:25.370
<i>NEWSCASTER:
And now some breaking news.</i>

28:25.437 --> 28:26.438
<i>The United Kingdom
authorities</i>

28:26.504 --> 28:28.239
<i>have confirmed
an important lead</i>

28:28.306 --> 28:29.974
<i>regarding the Almanzora girls.</i>

28:30.041 --> 28:31.643
<i>Let's hear
our London correspondent.</i>

28:31.710 --> 28:33.712
<i>Please tell us what the UK
authorities are saying.</i>

28:33.812 --> 28:36.281
ALVARO: What's that?

28:40.452 --> 28:44.189
♪♪♪

28:59.370 --> 29:02.440
- BEA: Javi.
- ALVARO: Javi?

29:02.507 --> 29:03.708
<i>NEWS REPORTER:
According to police sources,</i>

29:03.808 --> 29:06.077
<i>a witness recently saw
the Almanzora girls</i>

29:06.144 --> 29:09.013
<i>getting of a train in the
station in Wexford, Ireland.</i>

29:09.080 --> 29:11.049
<i>EUROPOL is
conducting a search</i>

29:11.116 --> 29:12.984
<i>It's the first lead about
the girls from Almanzora...</i>

29:13.084 --> 29:15.920
I knew it!
I knew they were safe!

29:15.987 --> 29:18.757
- Javi?
-<i> ...until this moment.</i>

29:18.823 --> 29:22.427
Wonderful news!
The three of them are alive!

29:22.527 --> 29:23.762
Yeah, I suppose.

29:23.828 --> 29:26.431
Then why aren't you putting
the flags out, bro?

29:26.531 --> 29:28.433
<i>...at Paraíso Nightclub
in the region of Almanzora.</i>

29:28.533 --> 29:31.269
-<i> Their families...</i>
- Javi, wait.

29:31.369 --> 29:33.171
My sister would never
just leave like that.

29:34.572 --> 29:36.508
Not calling,
keeping us in the dark,

29:36.608 --> 29:38.443
not knowing
if she's dead or alive.

29:38.510 --> 29:40.278
Maybe not, but it seems like
that's what she did.

29:40.345 --> 29:42.247
Chances are
the witness is wrong.

29:42.313 --> 29:44.549
But it was double-checked.
It was endorsed by the police.

29:44.649 --> 29:45.784
Don't you think
you're wigging out?

29:45.884 --> 29:48.753
No, Quino, I'm not wigging out,
you hear me?

29:48.853 --> 29:50.155
Maybe I didn't know her,

29:50.255 --> 29:52.290
and she kept secrets
from me, for sure,

29:52.357 --> 29:54.526
but I know she's not so cruel
to just lie to us

29:54.592 --> 29:55.994
to just go partying!

29:57.829 --> 29:58.596
Because that means
she doesn't love my father

29:58.663 --> 30:01.032
and she doesn't love me.

30:04.002 --> 30:05.703
I don't care if you don't
believe me, okay?

30:05.804 --> 30:06.971
I know it's a false story!

30:16.614 --> 30:19.117
[door slams]

30:27.725 --> 30:29.160
[distant sigh]

31:14.606 --> 31:17.308
- SANDRA:<i> Is it recording now?</i>
- MALENA:<i> No, it's not.</i>

31:17.408 --> 31:19.410
EVA:<i> Yes, it's recording.</i>
<i>You're touching it again.</i>

31:19.477 --> 31:21.312
<i>-</i> EVA:<i> Shh. Shh. Sorry.
-</i> SANDRA:<i> And now,</i>

31:21.412 --> 31:24.115
<i>ladies and gentlemen,
Sandra Merino,</i>

31:24.215 --> 31:25.950
<i>with an acapella version
of the best song</i>

31:26.050 --> 31:29.888
<i>- the world has ever heard.</i>
- [overlapping chatter]

31:29.954 --> 31:32.423
<i>Girls, girls, are you gonna
argue over this again?</i>

31:32.523 --> 31:34.025
<i>Just let her sing
whatever she wants.</i>

31:34.125 --> 31:35.994
<i>Fine, fine, go,
that's all right.</i>

31:36.094 --> 31:37.428
-<i> Ready.</i>
- [off-key singing]

31:37.528 --> 31:39.998
<i>Oh!</i>

31:40.064 --> 31:42.333
<i>Don't do that, girls.</i>

31:42.400 --> 31:44.469
<i>Please, girls,
let's do it right.</i>

31:44.569 --> 31:45.570
[off-key singing]

31:45.637 --> 31:48.406
<i>Let's do it right,
girls, come on.</i>

31:48.473 --> 31:51.175
<i>- Okay, sorry.
- Fine, okay, we'll do it right.</i>

31:51.242 --> 31:51.910
<i>Seriously.</i>

31:55.847 --> 31:59.984
[singing softly in Spanish]

32:06.524 --> 32:09.327
[singing continues]

32:27.745 --> 32:31.983
[singing continues]

32:41.793 --> 32:43.962
[singing continues]

32:46.597 --> 32:48.933
- What happened, Mario?
- It's all false, Costa.

32:49.000 --> 32:50.768
She didn't run away.

32:51.736 --> 32:55.873
[soft singing continues]

33:08.920 --> 33:10.755
[singing ends]

33:30.008 --> 33:32.877
[taps on glass]

33:36.647 --> 33:37.782
[tap on glass]

33:38.649 --> 33:39.784
[tap repeats]

33:46.090 --> 33:48.526
It's her favorite band,
you know?

33:48.593 --> 33:50.728
Well, actually,
I think it's everyone's.

33:50.795 --> 33:52.964
Yeah, but she's a big fan.

33:53.031 --> 33:54.198
Fan number one.

33:56.267 --> 33:57.668
Who would ever run away
two weeks before

33:57.769 --> 33:58.970
the concert of your life?

34:00.438 --> 34:01.005
I don't get it either.

34:08.146 --> 34:11.149
Javi, I heard a noise
on the cliff.

34:11.249 --> 34:14.085
- In Paraíso?
- Yeah, it sounded...

34:14.152 --> 34:15.486
like some kind of an animal.

34:15.553 --> 34:20.024
I heard it coming out of
the rocks by the cliff's wall.

34:20.124 --> 34:22.560
There's something
beneath that construction, Javi.

34:22.627 --> 34:23.928
We have to go back
and try to sneak in.

34:30.468 --> 34:32.670
- I know it's hard to believe--
- I really like you.

34:32.770 --> 34:35.373
Your. I like
your idea. I do.

34:45.149 --> 34:45.883
[distant door closes]

34:45.950 --> 34:49.053
MARIO:
Javi, I'm home!

34:49.120 --> 34:51.756
Well, let's bounce.
It's getting really late.

34:51.856 --> 34:54.158
We got a shoebox with a couple
of flashlights inside.

34:54.225 --> 34:55.226
We can always stop
by the hardware store.

34:55.326 --> 34:57.361
- It must be open.
- No, no, I'm sure

34:57.428 --> 35:00.031
I have one around here.
Let me...[grunts]

35:00.131 --> 35:01.866
I think I saw it.

35:05.870 --> 35:08.306
- Oh!
- Javi! Javi!

35:08.406 --> 35:11.242
- Are you okay?
- Shit. Shit, the paint!

35:11.309 --> 35:12.076
My sister's motorcycle.

35:17.081 --> 35:18.850
What the hell are you doing,
Javi?

35:20.051 --> 35:22.186
Everything you touch
goes to hell.

35:23.688 --> 35:26.157
- Please forgive me, I didn't--
- No! Just shut up!

35:26.224 --> 35:27.792
Get out of my sight!
Just shut it!

35:30.928 --> 35:32.763
You're nothing but a jerk.

35:38.703 --> 35:42.406
[door opens, closes]

36:02.026 --> 36:05.997
♪♪♪

36:55.913 --> 37:01.319
[horn honks, tires squeal]

37:05.089 --> 37:06.123
Bea! Get in the car!

37:06.190 --> 37:08.526
Please, Dad, let me do
this one thing.

37:08.593 --> 37:10.695
I swear that
I'll return in two hours.

37:10.761 --> 37:12.230
- Get in the car!
- Hey, let her go.

37:12.330 --> 37:13.431
- What are you doing?
- Let her go right now!

37:13.531 --> 37:14.198
- Let her go!
- Let me go!

37:14.265 --> 37:16.167
Do as I say and get in!

37:17.768 --> 37:18.903
- Get in.
- No.

37:19.003 --> 37:20.371
- Get in!
- I said no!

37:25.543 --> 37:27.511
I have told you I don't want you
going near that kid,

37:27.612 --> 37:28.913
or his family!

38:05.049 --> 38:08.085
[glass shatters]

38:09.687 --> 38:11.522
[clatter]

38:24.135 --> 38:25.903
Who's there?

38:36.947 --> 38:39.150
What are you doing here?

38:39.250 --> 38:40.251
ALVARO: That girlfriend
of yours called us.

38:40.318 --> 38:42.253
Does she ever
take a break or what?

38:42.320 --> 38:45.323
I'd love that,
but Bea isn't my girlfriend.

38:46.357 --> 38:49.527
I'm fine,
so just go home, guys.

38:49.593 --> 38:50.995
Javi, you do know
your sister.

38:52.363 --> 38:54.532
If you think
the police are mistaken,

38:54.598 --> 38:56.033
shame on them, bro.

38:56.133 --> 38:58.102
And we're sorry
we were jerks earlier.

38:59.470 --> 39:01.372
But jerks or not,
we're your friends.

39:01.439 --> 39:02.873
So that means you get
to put up with us.

39:02.973 --> 39:07.011
Wherever one goes,
well, we all go.

39:08.279 --> 39:09.914
No. This time you don't.

39:11.282 --> 39:12.717
What I'm about to do
is illegal.

39:12.783 --> 39:14.285
We might get in trouble.

39:15.319 --> 39:16.387
We're only 14, dude.

39:16.487 --> 39:17.955
It's not like
we're getting life for it.

39:21.158 --> 39:22.393
[Javi chuckles]

39:24.595 --> 39:26.364
[both chuckle]

39:30.968 --> 39:32.403
Come on, let's do this.

39:34.772 --> 39:36.974
- Ready?
- Yeah.

39:39.343 --> 39:41.112
[grunts]

40:00.765 --> 40:06.871
♪♪♪

40:12.410 --> 40:12.943
ALVARO:
This is incredible.

40:15.012 --> 40:16.414
[fluttering wings]

40:19.683 --> 40:21.152
There has to be
a switch somewhere.

40:31.295 --> 40:32.530
- [echoing click]
- [gasps] Shit!

40:32.596 --> 40:35.266
Please don't joke around!
It gives me the creeps!

40:36.634 --> 40:37.768
Javi?

40:37.835 --> 40:40.704
- Quino?
- [thudding]

40:43.574 --> 40:47.244
Look, man, I won't kill you
because I know you'd like it.

40:47.311 --> 40:49.046
I think I can get us
some music going.

40:51.816 --> 40:53.551
Boo-yah!

40:53.651 --> 40:54.919
The Cardigans?

40:55.386 --> 40:56.954
Faith?

41:00.157 --> 41:02.126
- [high-pitched whine]
- Cowabunga, Quino.

41:02.193 --> 41:04.361
- You're legit.
- Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

41:04.428 --> 41:05.329
- Oh, my God, hold it!
- What?

41:05.396 --> 41:08.032
Respect!

41:08.132 --> 41:10.134
What kind of name is OBK, dude?

41:10.201 --> 41:12.069
Uh, it's short for "Oberkorn."

41:12.169 --> 41:13.971
They took it
from a Depeche album.

41:14.038 --> 41:15.806
Play it now, dude.

41:22.413 --> 41:26.150
♪♪♪

41:35.826 --> 41:38.095
[OBK, "Historias de Amor"]

41:51.041 --> 41:55.012
[singing in Spanish]

42:17.635 --> 42:19.904
[volume increases]

42:35.352 --> 42:39.557
[singing in Spanish]

42:48.799 --> 42:50.601
Hey, you!

42:50.668 --> 42:52.770
You fucking faggot.

42:52.836 --> 42:54.171
What are you doing?

42:54.238 --> 42:55.606
- Finally got you, huh?
- Let him go!

42:55.673 --> 42:57.107
You gonna apologize?

42:57.207 --> 42:58.208
- Javi! Javi!
- Or should I cut

42:58.275 --> 42:59.410
your fucking tongue, you rat?

42:59.476 --> 43:01.345
- No, no!
- Leave him alone!

43:02.212 --> 43:04.648
Leave him alone, damn it!

43:04.715 --> 43:06.250
- [grunts]
- What are you doing?

43:06.317 --> 43:08.185
Just say it right now!

43:08.285 --> 43:10.154
No... [grunts]

43:10.254 --> 43:11.322
[knife clatters]

43:11.388 --> 43:13.490
- [blows land]
- [grunting]

43:13.557 --> 43:14.925
I'm gonna beat the shit
out of you

43:14.992 --> 43:16.527
so you know pain, moron!

43:16.594 --> 43:18.562
- [grunts]
- Help us! Javi!

43:25.235 --> 43:28.172
I'm kicking your guts
out of your ass!

43:28.238 --> 43:30.574
- [cries of pain]
- Alvaro! Quino!

43:33.043 --> 43:34.011
- You okay?
- Yeah.

43:36.313 --> 43:37.548
What's your problem, huh?

43:38.716 --> 43:40.050
What have we done to you?

43:40.117 --> 43:41.652
Why can't you just
leave us alone, man?

43:41.719 --> 43:43.520
'Cause you maggots ruined
my fucking life!

43:43.587 --> 43:45.356
[groans of pain]

43:45.456 --> 43:46.023
Mine is the one ruined!

43:48.225 --> 43:50.094
My sister has disappeared!

43:50.160 --> 43:50.928
Is your life that ruined?

43:53.130 --> 43:54.632
Do you care about anyone else?

43:54.732 --> 43:56.634
[groaning]

43:56.734 --> 43:58.135
[grunting, panting]

44:00.004 --> 44:01.271
Let's bounce.

44:02.206 --> 44:04.174
Come on, I found something.

44:11.749 --> 44:14.051
Over here, look at this.

44:17.688 --> 44:18.956
Is it a chest?

44:24.194 --> 44:25.496
You hear it?

44:31.468 --> 44:33.070
What are we supposed to hear?

44:35.606 --> 44:36.974
If you're staying,
don't be a hassle.

44:39.209 --> 44:40.878
[thudding]

44:40.944 --> 44:41.745
- What the hell was that?
- Let's find out. Help me.

44:41.845 --> 44:43.047
There's something down there.

44:46.684 --> 44:48.252
[effort grunts]

44:49.286 --> 44:50.988
What are you doing?

44:52.389 --> 44:54.591
I told you.
There is something.

44:54.692 --> 44:55.893
Down.

44:55.959 --> 44:57.227
- [exclaims]
- Oh.

44:57.327 --> 44:59.129
[landing thump]

45:05.602 --> 45:12.376
[far-off howling]

45:13.677 --> 45:15.079
I knew it, guys.

46:07.664 --> 46:09.333
Oh, God.

46:18.008 --> 46:19.610
It's very dark.

46:20.644 --> 46:22.880
Al! Here!

46:23.747 --> 46:24.915
JAVI: Give it here.

46:41.865 --> 46:44.835
Is this what you meant
by "caves in the pirate era"?

46:44.935 --> 46:46.303
If this is just a prank,

46:46.403 --> 46:48.205
I'll tear the balls
out of you three.

46:52.309 --> 46:55.445
[far-off howling]

46:59.249 --> 47:00.851
Guys, talk to me!

47:00.918 --> 47:02.953
[distant creaking]

47:12.930 --> 47:15.632
Hello? Hello?

47:21.205 --> 47:22.005
QUINO:
Don't take too long!

47:28.212 --> 47:31.148
[howling continues]

47:42.025 --> 47:44.027
I was worried that was Goku
becoming a giant monkey.

47:45.896 --> 47:47.464
I was right.
I was right!

47:47.564 --> 47:48.765
They took 'em out through here.

47:48.832 --> 47:50.434
They took them by force!

47:51.735 --> 47:53.904
ALVARO: Yeah, man,
I think you were right.

47:55.305 --> 47:56.506
Is that blood?

48:02.613 --> 48:04.715
No. No!

48:06.283 --> 48:08.051
[waves crashing]

48:09.086 --> 48:10.354
Right here.

48:13.757 --> 48:14.925
Take the light.

48:16.994 --> 48:18.362
[pounds on door]

48:32.910 --> 48:34.344
Oh, shit. Oh, shit!

48:34.444 --> 48:36.313
Fire! Guys!
There's a fire!

48:36.813 --> 48:38.749
Fire!

48:38.849 --> 48:41.318
Guys, there's a fire!

48:44.254 --> 48:47.190
Come up! There's a fire!
The place is burning!

48:47.291 --> 48:49.927
Hurry! Hurry, damn it!

48:54.464 --> 48:56.133
- Hurry.
- Careful!

48:57.167 --> 48:58.535
[coughing]

48:58.602 --> 48:59.603
QUINO: How do we get
out of here?

48:59.670 --> 49:00.671
JAVI: I don't know!

49:00.771 --> 49:02.639
[coughing continues]

49:03.907 --> 49:05.909
- Hurry up!
- Right behind you!

49:06.009 --> 49:07.911
JAVI: Open it up!

49:08.011 --> 49:11.315
[coughing]

49:11.415 --> 49:13.116
QUINO: Come on! Go!

49:16.086 --> 49:18.288
Whew! Oh, God damn it.

49:18.355 --> 49:19.957
Aah!

49:48.485 --> 49:49.886
ZETA:
We're fucked, man.

49:49.953 --> 49:51.722
QUINO: I shouldn't have
touched the wires!

49:51.788 --> 49:52.990
Let's get to the door!

49:53.090 --> 49:54.691
- To the door!
- Javi!

49:54.758 --> 49:56.393
[both exclaiming]

49:56.493 --> 49:58.562
- Over there!
- Hurry!

49:58.628 --> 50:00.530
Ohh!

50:01.798 --> 50:03.567
JAVI: Back to the tunnel!
To the tunnel!

50:03.633 --> 50:04.768
ZETA: Go back fast!

50:04.835 --> 50:07.571
JAVI: Run! Just run!
Come on!

50:12.409 --> 50:14.311
To the bathrooms!
It's full of tiles and water!

50:14.411 --> 50:16.246
- Come on!
- Javi! Look for a window!

50:22.853 --> 50:24.654
The towel, the towel!

50:28.225 --> 50:30.394
[coughing]

50:44.107 --> 50:45.442
[coughing]

50:45.509 --> 50:48.078
♪♪♪

51:18.208 --> 51:18.975
Hey, guys.

51:20.844 --> 51:22.646
How do you all feel?

51:23.680 --> 51:26.416
Okay, I guess.

51:28.251 --> 51:29.386
Where's Alvaro?

51:30.554 --> 51:32.355
He must've ran off
like the rat he is.

51:33.623 --> 51:35.525
Or he woke up
and went for help.

51:40.530 --> 51:42.933
[coughing]

51:56.446 --> 51:57.547
Oh, shit.

51:57.647 --> 52:00.083
Oh, shit.

52:00.150 --> 52:01.918
Oh, shit,
oh, shit, oh shit!

52:08.792 --> 52:10.994
MAN: Quickly!
They're over here!

52:15.966 --> 52:17.367
Oh, God.

52:43.693 --> 52:44.027
No one's here.

52:49.533 --> 52:52.135
Hey, guys, look.

52:52.202 --> 52:54.437
QUINO: Oh, God,
I really messed up.

52:54.504 --> 52:56.973
ZETA: I was not here, okay?
You never saw me.

53:08.151 --> 53:09.986
[phone rings]

53:12.756 --> 53:15.492
[phone rings]

53:17.093 --> 53:19.629
[phone continues ringing]

53:23.967 --> 53:25.268
Hello?

53:26.469 --> 53:28.171
Costa.

53:28.238 --> 53:29.706
What time is it?

53:48.391 --> 53:50.160
We must tell everyone.

53:51.528 --> 53:53.964
Costa! Costa!

53:54.030 --> 53:55.932
MAN: [echoing]
Go, set a perimeter!

53:58.001 --> 54:00.237
- [overlapping chatter]
- [siren blaring]

54:02.172 --> 54:04.074
How did they do that?

54:04.174 --> 54:05.675
MAN: [echoing]
Move it!

54:21.825 --> 54:23.793
MAN: [echoing] I'm sorry,
you can't go over there!

54:23.893 --> 54:25.729
Please step back!

54:32.569 --> 54:35.505
[overlapping, echoing shouts]

54:44.714 --> 54:46.483
Oh, my God, no!

54:49.586 --> 54:51.788
That's my dad!

54:51.888 --> 54:53.323
Hey, guess what?
We found a tunnel!

54:53.390 --> 54:55.358
I think they were smuggled
through the...

55:06.036 --> 55:09.706
♪♪♪

55:21.785 --> 55:25.488
[siren wailing]

55:38.234 --> 55:40.570
Let's go! Be careful
with the ceiling!

55:40.637 --> 55:42.205
Quickly!
They're over here!

55:48.144 --> 55:50.213
MAN: [echoing]
Someone's alive!

55:50.280 --> 55:52.048
This one is still breathing!

55:58.655 --> 56:01.725
[echoing shouts]

56:11.668 --> 56:14.604
[wailing]

56:17.707 --> 56:19.242
No fucking way.

56:20.744 --> 56:22.612
Are--are we dead?

56:22.679 --> 56:26.349
♪♪♪

56:46.836 --> 56:49.472
[distant bird cries]

56:55.678 --> 56:57.213
GIL PERÉZ [muttering]:
No, not here.

56:57.280 --> 56:59.115
These have to go there.

56:59.182 --> 57:01.584
Motherfucker got me.
What are you doing?

57:01.684 --> 57:03.953
You're doing it wrong.
It's all wrong.

57:10.560 --> 57:12.228
[door opens]

57:17.834 --> 57:19.235
Hello?

57:28.845 --> 57:30.647
Mr. Gil Peréz?

57:53.203 --> 57:54.304
I knew you were
one of them.

57:54.404 --> 57:57.373
I knew it right away,
you son of a bitch.

57:57.440 --> 57:58.975
You motherfucker,
you piece of--

57:59.042 --> 58:00.443
Don't turn! Don't move!

58:00.510 --> 58:02.345
Don't move or I'll shoot
your brains out!

58:03.847 --> 58:04.948
Didn't I--I warned you,
motherfucker!

58:05.048 --> 58:07.684
I told you I'd shoot
your brains out,

58:07.750 --> 58:09.319
you son of a bitch!
I told you!

58:09.385 --> 58:12.555
Didn't I warn you,
motherfucker?!

58:12.622 --> 58:13.790
Huh?!

58:18.728 --> 58:21.731
[gunshots]

58:23.733 --> 58:27.637
♪♪♪

58:37.013 --> 58:39.282
[thunder crashing]

58:40.984 --> 58:43.052
[thunder crashing]

58:54.430 --> 58:58.434
[singing in Spanish]
